A dataset consists of a set of Compounds
and a set of properties.
Note: Each property comes with
some conditions. If we query the property
called LC50 we will get all these LC50-related properties.
For example LC50 for fish, cows, mice etc... One might
need to query for THE particular LC50 they need
or specify a range, e.g. LC50 with x<10 where x is
an experimental condition.
Note: Each property actually refers to a group
of properties that are somehow related. One
should wary with the different underlying expe-
rimental conditions!!!
We may not need to specify
a condition if the property is not
